    <apex:form rendered="{!showSerach}">
        <apex:pageMessages ></apex:pageMessages>
        <apex:sectionHeader subtitle="Part Number Search" />
        <!--<div style="padding-left:87%"><a href="/apex/MDD_Reach" target="_blank" class="class1">Reach    </a><a href="/apex/MDD_ChinaRohs" target="_blank" class="class1">China ROHS</a></div>
        <hr></hr>-->
        <div>
            <p>The search function enables you to access material
            declarations for the parts you purchase from GLOBALFOUNDRIES.  For your convenience,
            there are two material declaration formats for each part - an GLOBALFOUNDRIES form
            material declaration and an IPC 1752-2 form declaration.</p>
            
            <p>The data within the declarations is not part-number specific.  Rather,
            the data applies to part-families.</p>
            
            <ul class="ibm-bullet-list">
              <li><strong>Wafers</strong>:  each part-family consists of wafers that GLOBALFOUNDRIES manufactured
            in any version of the same base process technology.  For example, wafers
            that GLOBALFOUNDRIES manufactured in any of its CMOS9 process technologies are in
            the same part-family.</li>
              <li><strong>Modules</strong>:  each part-family consists of modules: (1) containing
            chips that GLOBALFOUNDRIES manufactured in any version of the same base process
            technology, (2) with the same package type, and (3) containing the same
            bond and assembly materials (such as epoxies, solders, mold compounds,
            and lids).  For example, modules containing chips that GLOBALFOUNDRIES manufactured
            in any of its CMOS10 process technologies, with flip chip plastic ball grid
            array packages, and containing the same bond and assembly materials, are in
            the same part-family.</li>
            </ul>
            
            <p>For modules, the data within each declaration is based on the maximum
            chip and package size within a part-family. In addition, and also for modules,
            the data in each declaration is based on the maximum number of each passive
            component (i.e., capacitors and resistors) possible for a part within that
            family, as determined by GLOBALFOUNDRIES design ground rules.</p>
            
            <p>You can search by GLOBALFOUNDRIES part number or your part number, and for either
            single or multiple part numbers.  If searching by GLOBALFOUNDRIES part number, you do
            not need to enter any "0's" at the beginning of the part number.  You can
            limit a search to wafers or modules.  For modules, you can further
            restrict search results by package type.</p>
            
            <p>Search results are limited to 100 part numbers.</p>
            <hr></hr>
            <h1>Part Number Search </h1>
        </div>
        <div style="padding-left:50px">
        <b>Part Number(s) : </b><apex:inputText required="true" label="Part Number(s)" size="20" value="{!PartNumber}" title="Part Number(s)"/>
        </div>
        <div style="padding-left:50px;padding-top:10px">
        <div style="width:10%;float:left;padding-top:5px"><b>Limit Search To:</b></div>
        <div style="width:15%;float:left"><apex:inputCheckbox label="Wafers" value="{!isWafer}"/> Wafers </div>
        <div style="width:15%;float:left"><apex:inputCheckbox label="Modules" value="{!isModule}"/> Modules </div>
        </div><br></br>
        <div><br></br>
        <div style="padding-left:50px;padding-top:10px">
        <b>Module Package Type : </b>
        <apex:selectList size="1" value="{!getPackageType}" styleClass="pickCls" title="Select a package type">
          <!--<apex:selectOptions value="{!Package}" />
          <apex:selectOption itemDisabled="true" itemValue="Select a package type" itemLabel="Select a package type"/>-->
          <apex:selectOption itemDisabled="true" itemLabel=" "/>
          <apex:selectOption itemDisabled="true" itemValue="Flip Chip Ceramic" itemLabel="Flip Chip Ceramic" />
          <apex:selectOption itemValue="CBGA" itemLabel="CBGA" />
          <apex:selectOption itemValue="CCGA" itemLabel="CCGA" />
          <apex:selectOption itemValue="CLGA" itemLabel="CLGA" />
          <apex:selectOption itemDisabled="true" itemValue="Flip Chip Organic" itemLabel="Flip Chip Organic" />
          <apex:selectOption itemValue="FC PBGA" itemLabel="FC PBGA" />
          <apex:selectOption itemValue="FC PLGA" itemLabel="FC PLGA" />
          <apex:selectOption itemValue="FCPBGA HP" itemLabel="FCPBGA HP" />
        </apex:selectList></div>
        </div>
        <br></br>
        
        <apex:commandButton action="{!search}" value="Search" />
        <div>
            <p><em>Ask questions or submit comments about material declarations to
            GLOBALFOUNDRIES Chemical Management Program Manager:</em></p>
            <ul>
            <li>{!$Label.contactEmail}</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </apex:form>
    <apex:form rendered="{!showSerachResult}">
        <apex:sectionHeader subtitle="Search Result Summary" title=""/><br></br>
        <!--<div style="padding-left:87%"><a href="/apex/MDD_Reach" target="_blank" class="class1">Reach    </a><a href="/apex/MDD_ChinaRohs" target="_blank" class="class1">China ROHS</a></div>
        <hr></hr>-->
        <div style="font-size:1.166em;"><h1>Summary Part Number Report </h1></div><br></br>
        <div>
            <div style="width:48%;float:left;">
            <b>Search Strings:</b>{!PartNumber}
            </div>
            <div>
            <b>Results Limited To:</b><apex:outputText value="{!if(isWafer == true,"Wafer","Module")}" rendered="{!if(((isWafer == true && isModule == false) || (isWafer == false && isModule == true)),true,false)}"/>
                                <apex:outputText value="Wafer,Module" rendered="{!if(isWafer == true && isModule == true,true,false)}"/>
            </div><br></br>
            <div style="width:48%;float:left;">
            <b>Package Type:</b>{!getPackageType}
            </div><br></br><br></br>
            <a href="#" onclick="history.go(-1)" class="class1"><apex:image id="d1" value="{!$Resource.MDD_DeclarationBack}" width="15" height="13" alt="back" /> Modify Search</a><br></br>
            <p>By clicking a part number in the table, you import the GLOBALFOUNDRIES form material
            declaration for that part into a table for your review, and you also create
            a link through which you can view and download the IPC-1752-2 form material
            declaration as an XML file.</p>
            <p>For certain modules there may be multiple part family information available
            for an individual module part number. The multiple part family information is provided
            because the module is built at multiple bond and assembly locations, and each
            location uses different bond and assembly materials (such as epoxies, mold
            compounds, solders, and lids) for the build of this module part number thereby
            leading to multiple part family information. For complete material content
            declaration information please click and download all available part family
            options provided for each module part number.</p>
        </div>
        <apex:pageBlock >
            <apex:pageBlockTable value="{!lstPart}" var="p" rendered="{!lstPart.size!=0}">
                <apex:column headerValue="Part Number">
                 <a href="{!gfView}/apex/MDD_Part_Info?partId={!p.Id}" >{!p.Part_Number__c}</a>
                </apex:column>
                <apex:column headerValue="Part Family">
                    <label>{!p.MDPart_Family__c}</label>
                </apex:column>
                <apex:column headerValue="Part Type" value="{!p.Part_Type__c}"></apex:column>
                <apex:column headerValue="Last Updated" value="{!p.LastModifiedDate}"></apex:column>
            </apex:pageBlockTable>
            <apex:outputPanel rendered="{!lstPart.size==0}">
                <p class="p">The search found no part numbers matching your search criteria.</p>
            </apex:outputPanel>
        </apex:pageBlock>
    </apex:form>
</apex:page>